title: Road Map to Week 8's most intriguing college football games
text:
Utah running back Devontae Booker (23) receives a hug from teammate Sam Tevi, center, and Kenneth Scott (2) in a win against Arizona State on Oct. 17. The Utes are unbeaten and leading contenders for the Playoff. (Photo: Rick Bowmer, AP)
CONNECT 21 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE This week's slate doesn't look too impressive on paper â€” especially coming off last Saturday's action. But these are the weeks that tend to produce a surprising result or two. Several top teams are on the road and could be in danger of tripping up before what should be a wild month of November.
With 13 FBS teams still without a loss, could this be the week the playoff picture starts to clear itself up?
Welcome to the Football Four's Road Map, a weekly introduction to the most intriguing matchups of the weekend. We'll give you a look across the college football landscape and break down the games you cannot afford to miss.
